# App listing automation (agent-owned)

The user must **never** be asked to run `register-app`, `create-app`, or manual listing commands for:

- Store legal hub: `personal-site` (Vercel) — App Store / Play
- Portfolio works list: `ymd-portfolio` (Cloudflare Pages) — Web-only, no store review

## When this applies

Creating a new app, deploying a Web app, preparing App Store / Play submission, or adding something to the portfolio.

## What you must do (you, the agent)

### Web-only (portfolio)

1. Run `ymd-portfolio/scripts/publish-app-listing.mjs --name "..." --url "https://..."`.
2. Embed privacy/terms/support links in the app footer (`docs/WEB_PUBLISH.md`).
3. Confirm https://ymd-portfolio-site.pages.dev/

### Store submission (legal hub)

1. Register store hub via `personal-site/tools/publish-app-listing.mjs` (or register-app).
2. If a public Web URL exists, portfolio registration is included when `--url` is passed.
3. Commit / push / deploy; confirm live URLs.

## Do not

- Tell the user “run this npm command to register”.
- Leave registration as a follow-up for the user.
- Confuse the portfolio (https://ymd-portfolio-site.pages.dev/) with the store legal hub (https://personal-site-taupe-gamma.vercel.app/).
